==================================================
CHANGE — Final hexagonal package cleanup + docs refresh
Date: 2026-03-30
==================================================

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Finish the transitional architecture cleanup so the repository reads like a
real ports-and-adapters system on first sight, then update the docs and prompt
history to match the final structure.

==================================================
WHAT CHANGED
==================================================

1. PACKAGE CLEANUP

  Moved:
    internal/judge/                 -> internal/domain/judge/
    internal/timer/                 -> internal/infrastructure/localtimer/
    internal/registry/              -> internal/infrastructure/registry/
    internal/personalization/       -> internal/application/personalization/

  Removed empty transitional packages:
    internal/events/
    internal/problemset/
    internal/recommendation/

2. FINAL INTERNAL SHAPE

  internal/
    adapter/
    application/
      personalization/
    domain/
      judge/
    infrastructure/
      localtimer/
      postgres/
      queue/
      registry/
      sandbox/
    port/
      in/
      out/

3. IMPORT / WIRING CLEANUP

  Updated:
    - application evaluation service to use internal/domain/judge
    - local-agent adapter to use infrastructure/localtimer
    - local-agent sync flow to use infrastructure/registry

  Result:
    - no leftover imports to the old mixed top-level packages
    - top-level internal folders now represent layers, not random concerns

4. MOCKS

  Mockery v3 output now lives with the split ports:
    internal/port/in/mocks/
    internal/port/out/mocks/

  Generic leftover mock package output was removed.

5. DOCS

  Updated:
    README.md
    docs/architecture.md
    docs/local-agent.md

  Docs now describe:
    - GORM + goose under infrastructure/postgres
    - split inbound/outbound ports
    - adapter vs infrastructure responsibilities
    - final local-agent package placement

==================================================
CURRENT STATE
==================================================

- cmd packages are entrypoints and wiring only
- application contains use cases
- domain contains entities and pure judge logic
- outbound dependencies are explicit through port/out
- inbound application API is explicit through port/in
- infrastructure naming reflects actual technologies
- docs and prompt history now match the code layout

